## F.23 A closing observation

Introspection makes teaching easier because it makes the language *self-teaching*. A learner with the introspection reflex can explore a namespace on their own. They can look up a verb on their own. They can debug their own errors. The teacher becomes a guide to the reflex, not a walking documentation site.

That shift is what makes Motoi worth teaching. The tool teaches with you.

## F.24 A closing exercise for teachers

For your next teaching session, prepare no lecture. Instead, prepare a short list of questions the learner can answer using introspection. Sit with them at the REPL. Ask a question. Wait. Guide them to the primitive.

You will find they learn faster. They will find they need you less. Both outcomes are good.

